                    <outline text="Abstract #abstract">
                        <outline text="Increasingly, data created or consumed by mobile apps is stored on cloud platforms. In order to ensure confidentiality, integrity and availability, encryption can be used but key distribution and management is difficult, especially if no public key infrastructures are available (IoT #jc not defined). Secret sharing is an attractive alternative to encryption in this scenario #jc unconditional SS?."/>
                        <outline text="This paper is concerned with secret sharing techniques for mobile cloud environments, with a focus on efficient share combining. "/>
                        <outline text="It is shown that the use of barycentric interpolation ( #jc what is the rational? why is an alternative needed? Which properties of barycentric interpolation suggest it has the potential of doing a better job?) developed in numerical mathematics can be used for cryptographic purposes, using finite field arithmetic. We have implemented the algorithm for desktop and mobile platforms and show that the performance is superior to standard techniques using Lagrange interpolation."/>
