                        <outline text="Basic Techniques in the Literature">
                            <outline text="Shamir Secret Sharing">
<outline text="Shamir -- Polynomial evaluation and interpolation"/>
<outline text="$$f(x) = s + \sum_{l=1}^{k-1}a_{l}x^{l}$$ where $$a_{l}$$ random elements of $$F_p$$ -- the Shamir polynomial "/>
<outline text="Within the secret sharing protocol follow 3 stages: share creation, share distribution and share combining."/>
<outline text="Share creation. ">
    <outline text="Choose $$n$$ distinct values $$x_{1},\ldots, x_{n}$$"/>
    <outline text="Compute shares as $$s_i = (x_{i},f(x_{i}))$$"/>
</outline>
<outline text="Distribution/Dealing"/>
<outline text="Share Combining">
    <outline text="From any coalition of size $$k$$   $$(x_{i_1},\cdots , x_{i_k})$$ and $$(f\left ( x_{i_1}\right ), \cdots , f\left ( x_{i_k}\right ))$$ we can reconstruct $$f$$ (and hence $$s = f\left ( 0 \right )$$) through interpolation."/>
</outline>
                            </outline>
                            <outline text="Ramp">
<outline text="Ramp -- Use all coefficients"/>
<outline text="$$f(x) = \sum_{l=0}^{k-1}s^{(l)}x^{l}$$ where $$s=s^{(0)}||\ldots||s^{(k-1)}$$ are the secret data, seen as elements of $$F_p$$ -- a generalisation of the Shamir polynomial, storing data in all coefficients"/>
<outline text="Blakeley -- Intersecting hyperplanes, in fact a specific instance of ramp [Blakley]"/>
                            </outline>
                        </outline>
                    </outline>
                    <outline text="Mobile Secret Sharing Architectures #h1">
                        <outline text="In this section, we discuss secret sharing architectures in a mobile setting. Depending on which stage of the secret sharing protocol is implemented on the mobile device, we differentiate between mobile dealer, mobile shareholder and mobile combiner, or a combination of these in a hybrid architecture. #jc it is unclear what is so special about the mobile configuration?"/>
                        <outline text="Use of Secret Sharing for Cloud Security">
